
@startuml
' Class Diagram for House System

class House {
  -address: String
  -buildingMaterial: String (wood, brick, concrete)
  -hasBasement: Boolean
  -basement: Basement
}

class Basement {
  -name: String
  -size: Double
}

class EarthBasement <|-- Basement
class ConcreteBasement <|-- Basement

EarthBasement {
  -humidityLevel: Double
}

ConcreteBasement {
}

class SemiDetachedHouse <|-- House
SemiDetachedHouse {
  -hasGarden: Boolean
  -numWindows: Integer
  -parking: Parking
}

abstract class Parking {
  -type: String
}

class Carport <|-- Parking
class Garage <|-- Parking

Carport {
  -isDouble: Boolean
  -hasFlatRoof: Boolean
}

Garage {
  -hasAutomaticDoor: Boolean
}

class Company {
  -name: String
  -address: String
}

class JobLog {
  -company: Company
  -house: House
  -hours: Integer
  -agreedPrice: Double
}

' Associations
House "1" *-- "0..*" Company : serviced by
House "1" *-- "0..1" Basement : has
SemiDetachedHouse "1" -- "1" Parking : has
Company "1" *-- "0..*" JobLog : performs job in
@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **`House`** is the base class with attributes like `address`, `buildingMaterial`, and possibly a `Basement`.
- **`Basement`** is an abstract class with two subclasses: **`EarthBasement`** (with humidity) and **`ConcreteBasement`**.
- **`SemiDetachedHouse`** is a subclass of `House` with additional attributes like `hasGarden`, `numWindows`, and a `Parking` object.
- **`Parking`** is an abstract class with two subclasses: **`Carport`** (double, flat roof) and **`Garage`** (automatic door).
- **`Company`** stores name and address.
- **`JobLog`** links a company to a house and records hours and price.

